====================================
  Building the GDA Developer Guide
====================================

Building the document requires both Sphinx and the Python module 'recommonmark'. These must be installed and set up in a Python virtual environment.


1) To create a virtual environmnet in Python 2 use the command:
    $ virtualenv gda_doc_venv

  For Python 3 instead use:
    $ python -m venv gda_doc_venv

2) Activate this virtual environment:
    $ source gda_doc_venv/bin/activate

3) Install Sphinx Within the virtual environment:
    $ pip install -U sphinx


4) Install the 'recommonmark' module into the same virtual environment ($ source gda_doc_venv/bin/activate):
    $ pip install recommonmark

5) Now build:
  	$ cd workspace_git/gda-core.git/documentation.gda/GDA_Developer_Guide
  	$ make html
  

* Whenever building the documentation, remember to source the Python environment otherwise it will fail.